<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="dd04b437-00ff-4340-b9d6-22ca0379ba82" >

    <h2>Additional resources if you want to quit smoking or vaping</h2> 
<p>We recognize that tobacco and nicotine are addictive substances and we are committed to providing access to smoking reduction and cessation programs and education. Ryerson offers support for faculty, staff and students who want to quit smoking. If you are interested in quitting, the following are resources at Ryerson:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/healthandwellness/healthpromotion/sharp/body/">Smoking cessation resources for students</a></li> 
 <li><a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/hr/work-life/wellbeing-at-work/efap/">Employee and Family Assistance Program for employees</a></li> 
</ul> 
<h3>External resources</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><a href="http://www.leavethepackbehind.org./">Leave The Pack Behind (LTPB)<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a></li> 
 <li><a href="https://www.camh.ca/en/your-care/programs-and-services/nicotine-dependence-clinic">Nicotine Dependence Clinic at CAMH<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a></li> 
 <li><a href="http://www.tobaccowise.com">Cancer Care Ontario’s Aboriginal Tobacco Strategy<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a></li> 
 <li><a href="http://otru.org/">Ontario Tobacco Research Unit<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a></li> 
</ul>
    





